# Harness review bridge (Issue #658 / #683)

When AO spawns you as the **codex harness reviewer** for a worker PR, submit
findings using pack-contract structured JSON with `[P0]`–`[P3]` title prefixes
and `severity: blocking|non-blocking` in finding bodies — not prose `Finding:` /
`BLOCKING:` headings.

## Post-submit enforcement (Issue #683)

Pack enforcement is **post-submit**: after AO auto-submits your run, the pack
validates `latestRun.body` on the daemon poll loop (#669 substrate). Prose or
non-mapper bodies are rejected and the review is re-triggered until the terminal
state converges to `[Pn]`/mapper shape or escalates. Do not rely on this rule
file reaching your session — correctness is enforced on the observable run body.

## Optional bridge (mapper helper)

You may run the pack-owned harness bridge from the **trusted pack root** before
submit to produce mapper-shaped JSON (best-effort; not the enforcement seam):

```powershell
pwsh -NoProfile -File scripts/harness-review-bridge.ps1 `
  -RunId <review-run-id> `
  -RepoRoot . `
  -Base origin/main `
  -TrustedBaseRoot <trusted-pack-root>
```

`<trusted-pack-root>` is `AO_TRUSTED_PACK_ROOT`, an origin/main pack worktree, or the
operator's live pack checkout — **not** the PR head worktree under review.

Set `PACK_HARNESS_BRIDGE_DISABLED=1` to abort before submit (classified failure).

## Clean reviews

Zero-finding reviews must submit the shipped clean contract (`verdict: clean`,
`findingCount: 0`) — never an empty body or prose `LGTM`.
